Scripts I'm writing to set up Arch on my machines faster, following the wiki.

In its current form, these scripts
-install zen-kernel
-install pkgstats
-activate reflector with default settings
-will install in spanish (MX) and a latin-america kb layout
-asume an Intel processor
-set up a 2GiB boot partition (i like kernels)
-set up a 2GiB swap space
-install pipewire
-activate bootctl auto-update (i.e. require disabling SecureBoot)
-disabe hibernation
-activate modprobed-db

They will not
-allow dual booting (at least not using the same physical disk)
-encrypt storage or swap space
-configure sudoers.conf automatically
-enable additional repos
-set up nvidia or amd gpu drivers

Use at your own risk.
